# Project ERD & Workflow Quick Reference

Use this compact rule on every task as a fast mental model.
When needed, rely on `project-erd-and-workflow.mdc` for full details.

## Core Domain Map

- Identity: `users` (Spatie roles: `admin`, `professional`, `patient`).
- Multi-tenant context: `workspaces` + `workspace_members` (membership roles `member` / `billing_manager` — not Spatie).
- Professional metadata: `professional_profiles` (one row per professional user).
- Patient domain: `patient_profiles` + `case_assignments` (patient user ↔ professional ↔ optional workspace).
- Scheduling: `services` + `availabilities` + `appointments`.
- Session artifacts: `session_recordings`, `notes`, `agreements`, `consent_forms`, `documents`, `kosmo_briefings`.
- Billing: `invoices` + `invoice_items`.
- Communication: `messages` (optional `related` morph).
- Collaboration & intake: `collaboration_agreements`, `referrals`.

## Critical FK Semantics

1. `appointments.patient_id`, `invoices.patient_id`, `case_assignments.patient_id` → `users.id` (patient as user).
2. `notes.patient_id`, `agreements.patient_id`, `consent_forms.patient_id`, `documents.patient_id`, `kosmo_briefings.patient_id`, `referrals.patient_id` → `patient_profiles.id` (clinical profile row).
3. Prefer explicit naming in code/comments when switching between patient user vs patient profile identity.

## Workflow Snapshot

1. Auth + role resolution.
2. Professional onboarding + workspace context (`workspace` routes, `EnsureWorkspaceAccess` where applied).
3. Patient creation (`users` + `patient_profiles`; assignments via `case_assignments` as needed).
4. Agenda setup (`services`, `availabilities`).
5. Appointment lifecycle (`appointments`).
6. Session operations (call, transcription/summary, documentation).
7. Billing generation and follow-up (`invoices`, `invoice_items`).
8. Portal patient actions (view records, sign consent, join/cancel appointment, messages).

## Non-Negotiable Consistency Rules

- Preserve workspace scoping where `workspace_id` exists.
- Keep billing line/header integrity (`invoice_items` always tied to `invoices`).
- Protect role boundaries (`admin` vs `professional` vs `patient`).
- Validate status transitions end-to-end (appointments, invoices, consent forms).
- Update tests/factories/policies when relationships or flows change.
